.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH oxiarc-add 1  "oxiarc-add " 
.SH NAME
oxiarc\-add \- Add files to an existing archive (ZIP, TAR, LZH)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoxiarc\-add\fR [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-compression\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIARCHIVE\fR> [\fIFILES\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add files to an existing archive (ZIP, TAR, LZH)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-compression\fR \fI<COMPRESSION>\fR [default: normal]
Compression level (used when the archive format supports it)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
store: Store without compression
.IP \(bu 2
fast: Fast compression
.IP \(bu 2
normal: Normal compression (default)
.IP \(bu 2
best: Best compression
.RE
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose output
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Dry run: show planned changes without modifying the archive
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIARCHIVE\fR>
Existing archive file to append to
.TP
[\fIFILES\fR]
Files to add to the archive
